# Build-context exclusions for the sandbox base image (sandbox/base-image/Dockerfile, built from the
# repo root by .github/workflows/sandbox-image-release.yml).
#
# TRUST-TIER HYGIENE: this image runs UNTRUSTED agent code; its build stage (`COPY . .` then
# `go build ./sandbox/...`) must not ingest the OTHER tiers' source. The build only compiles
# `sandbox/policyhelper/...`, which imports `sdk/interfaces` and nothing else (verified), so we keep
# `sandbox/`, `sdk/`, `go.mod`, `go.sum` and exclude everything that is neither imported nor a build
# input — notably the key-broker and control-plane source. That source is public OSS (no secret
# leak either way), but keeping it out of the build context also keeps it out of the public
# `--provenance=mode=max` attestation, and honours the distinct-build-identity separation the image
# itself advertises. (If a future sandbox import reaches into another tier, the build fails loudly —
# the intended signal to reconsider that dependency.)
.git
.gitignore
control-plane
keybroker
providers
conformance
deploy
docs
scripts
.github
.claude
